      • toBCoverage

        public static java.util.List<BCoveragePackage> toBCoverage(java.util.List<CoveragePackage> packages,
                                           java.io.File baseDir)
                                                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Goes through all the coverage information, and searches the local filesystem. This is because BlueJ does not provide BPackages for packages that are not currently open in the GUI. If the Filestystem search is unable to locate the file, then the coverage information is excluded.
        Parameters:
        packages - all collected coverage information.
        baseDir - the base directory to search from
        Returns:
        the mapped coverage information
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • findFile

        private static java.io.File findFile(java.io.File base,
                    CoverageClass clz)
                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Tries to find a class file using base as the root directory to start searching from.

        If no file is found null is returned.

        Parameters:
        base - the base directory for the search
        clz - Information about the class to find, like name, and package.
        Returns:
        File containing the source code for the class defined in clz.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
